  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Deepening Transparancy and Accountability in the collection and use of District Assembly IGF</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">An increased in Citizens awareness of the process interested, committed and empowered to demand for transparency in the use of the IGF.
 2. An increase in citizen&#x2019;s awareness on district assembly revenue mobilization processes to enhance their capacity to demand transparency and accountability in the collection and use of the internally generated funds.
 3.An  Efficient utilization of internal generated Fund in the project Districts
 4. To contribute to an increase in the revenue of project districts through a reduction in revenue leakages.
5. A  reduction in the collection of unapproved tax by 60% as a result of increased awareness</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is intended to use a three-pronged approach/strategy to deliver on its outcomes: Social Audit Module/pictorial evidence method; Mobile/Web-based application; and Alliance Buildering Approach (ABA). The following activities will be carried out: development of a mobile-based application; training of revenue collectors on the use application; training of the MMDAs staff on the use of the platform and analysis; launching of mobile application; provision of computers and mobile phones; development of a project website to disseminate project information</narrative>
  </description>
